    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "FAQ & TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE"
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "Question",
      "__EMPTY": "Answer"
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "Can I use any camera with any VTX?",
      "__EMPTY": "Yes! All analog cameras (Caddx, RunCam, Foxeer) are compatible with all analog VTX (Eachine, TBS, Rush). Just connect video signal, power, and ground."
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "Can I use any VTX with any goggles?",
      "__EMPTY": "Yes! As long as both support 5.8GHz and are set to the same frequency/channel. Frequency matching is critical."
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "What if my goggles don't receive video?",
      "__EMPTY": "1) Check frequency matches between VTX and goggles. 2) Verify antenna connections. 3) Check camera power/video output. 4) Try different channel. 5) Check receiver module sensitivity."
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "Can I upgrade my goggle receiver?",
      "__EMPTY": "Yes! Goggles with modular bays (FatShark, Skyzone models with module bay) can use aftermarket modules like RapidFire for better range/performance."
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "What voltage should I use for cameras?",
      "__EMPTY": "Check camera specs. Most nano cameras: 3.3-5.5V. Most standard cameras: 5-36V. Use appropriate BEC or voltage regulator."
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "Which goggle brand is best?",
      "__EMPTY": "FatShark Dominator (most expensive but best). Skyzone SKY04X (best value premium). Eachine EV800D (best budget). All work with all analog VTX/cameras."
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "Can I use analog goggles with DJI drones?",
      "__EMPTY": "No. DJI/Walksnail/HDZero are digital systems. Analog goggles cannot receive digital signals (except DJI Goggles RE which can receive analog)."
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "What is the best beginner setup?",
      "__EMPTY": "Caddx Ant camera + Eachine TX805 VTX + FatShark Echo goggles = ~$150 total. All fully compatible, reliable, proven."
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "How far can analog FPV reach?",
      "__EMPTY": "400mW-800mW in open sky: 1-3km typical. 1000mW power: 3-5km+. Limited by antenna quality and line of sight."
    },
    {
      "ANALOG FPV CAMERAS": "What's better: Box or Headset goggles?",
      "__EMPTY": "Headset: Better ergonomics, better optics, more immersive but pricey. Box: Budget friendly, less comfortable, good for learning. Choose based on budget."
    }
